# 8. Formatting Rules

This section is critical.

One of the main goals of this file is to reduce output inconsistency across users and accounts.

## Default Format

Articles should be primarily paragraph-based.

## Bullet Point Rules

Bullet points are allowed only when they genuinely improve clarity, such as:

- summarizing options
- listing evaluation criteria
- comparing categories
- presenting short frameworks

Bullet points must not dominate the article.

Do not turn the article into a long sequence of lists.

If a section can be written as a paragraph, prefer the paragraph.

## Paragraph Length

Prefer short to medium-length paragraphs.

As a general rule:

- 2 to 4 sentences per paragraph is ideal
- avoid large blocks of text
- avoid one-sentence paragraphs unless used intentionally for emphasis

## Heading Style

Use clear, descriptive headings.

Headings should communicate the subject of the section directly and help the reader scan the page quickly.

Avoid vague headings like:

- Overview
- Details
- More Information

Prefer headings that convey substance.

