# 13. Common Mistakes to Avoid

Avoid the following:

- too many bullet points
- generic IT marketing language
- vague claims without operational relevance
- over-explaining simple concepts
- sounding like a software vendor instead of a strategic partner
- writing with too much feature language and not enough business context
- writing in a way that could apply to any MSP in any industry
- forgetting the media and entertainment angle
- losing narrative flow

A good GPL article should not feel interchangeable with content from a generic managed services company.

